s/2020/10/2ADK8AA-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> 2012&#39;s <em>Skyfall</em> has been name the best <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/james-bond">James Bond</a> film ever in a new survey.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/no-time-to-die-review-james-bond-3057021">&#39;No Time To Die&#39; review: Daniel Craig&#39;s surprisingly emotional final fling</a></strong></li></ul><p> Conducted in the UK by William Hill Vegas, the survey polled 3,500 fans of the franchise, asking them to name their favourite 007 movies from best to worst.</p><p> <em>Skyfall</em> , starring <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/daniel-craig">Daniel Craig</a> , topped the list with 17.5 percent of the vote, far ahead of the second-placed <em>Goldfinger</em> (8.5 percent), starring the late Sean Connery. Craig&#39;s final entry, <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/no-time-to-die"><em>No Time To Die</em></a> , came in at third with 7 percent.</p><p> Meanwhile, Connery&#39;s last outing as 007, <em>Never Say Never Again</em> , was voted the worst Bond film of all time, with just 0.6 percent of the vote.</p><p> <em>Skyfall</em> was both a critical and commercial success, grossing over $1.1 billion at the global box office and earning a critical rating of 92 percent on review aggregator site Rotten Tomatoes.</p><p> The film won two Oscars for Best Original Song and best Sound Editing, while also receiving multiple Grammys, a Golden Globe and a Screen Actors Guild Award. </p><figure id="attachment_2869708" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2869708" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-2869708" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench.jpg" alt="'Skyfall' Daniel Craig and Judi Dench" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Skyfall-Daniel-Craig-and-Judi-Dench-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2869708" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Skyfall&#39; Daniel Craig and Judi Dench. Credit: AA Film Archive/Alamy Stock Photo</figcaption></figure><p> Directed by Sam Mendes, <em>Skyfall</em> saw MI6 attacked, with Bond tracing the events back to a cyberterrorist named Raoul Silva (Javier Bardem).</p><p> The full synopsis reads: “When James Bond&#39;s ;atest assignment goes terribly wrong, it leads to a calamitous turn of events: undercover agents around the world are exposed, and MI6 is attacked, forcing M (Judi Dench) to relocate the agency.</p><p> “With MI6 now compromised inside and out, M turns to the one man she can trust: Bond. Aided only by a field agent (Naomie Harris), Bond takes to the shadows and follows a trail to Silva (Javier Bardem), a man from M&#39;s past who wants to settle an old score.</p><p> Following the end of Craig&#39;s tenure as 007, rumours about his successor have been rife. Aaron Taylor-Johnson has emerged as <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/theres-new-favourite-to-be-next-james-bond-3480092">one of the favourites to take over the role</a> , alongside Snowfall&#39;s Damson Idris, Bridgerton star Regé-Jean Page, Happy Valley star James Norton and Henry Cavill.</p><p> This week, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/aaron-taylor-johnson-wont-deny-james-bond-rumours-in-new-interview-3483188">Taylor-Johnson refused to deny rumours that he will be the next James Bond</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/this-is-the-best-james-bond-film-ever-according-to-fans-3484582">This is the best James Bond film ever, according to fans</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
